ProgramServiceAccomplishment.DescriptionProgramServiceAccom: During the year, the money that was raised and used to support the organization allowed the organization to provide meals to over 4,034 individuals, clothing and food for 1,594 poor and needy, and special events under the Family Impact Initiatives program.

Turnaround Community Outreach provides assistance to the homeless in obtaining a state issue photo ID. In 2010 we served 223 individuals.Various special events such as:Sunny's Back to School Dayz Event - In 2010 we served 521 people and the goal is to:1. Provide books and school clothing for low income families with children.2. Educate children that are having problems reading and show them the tools in the community that can help them.3. Get children that are kindergarten age signed up for school. Thanksgiving Event - In 2010 we served hot meals to 390 people and gave groceries to 408 families and individuals and the goal is to:1. Provide a hot meal to homeless and elderly individuals that can not get a hot meal for themselves.2. Provide a fun and family atmosphere for people that may not have a family to go to for Thanksgiving.3. Provide groceries to those in need so they can prepare their own Thanksgiving meal. Women's Event - In 2010 we served 55 people and the goal is to:1. Provide encouragement and community support to women that are in shelters or half-way houses2. Provide information that can be used to help these women when they are eventually living independent of a shelter3. Provide a nice, healthy meal and to teach them how to use resources in the community if in need of food4. Give personal hygiene items to each woman that attends the event Men's Event - In 2010 we served 95 people and the goal is to:1. Show homeless men coping skills and to educate them on how to be self- sufficient2. Provide a hot meal to men that are homeless or disabled3. Provide free hair cuts and clothing for job interviews 4. Provide basic hygiene items such as soap, tooth paste, combs Clothing for Teen & Baby Program - In 2010 we served 128 people and the goal is to:1. Educate teen parents about where to go in the community when they have needs and provide them with a support system to help them with their babies.2. Create a guide for teen parents to learn how to utilize the community if in need of help for their babies.3. Use local agencies, hospitals, etc. to educate the teen and family about nutrition, baby check-ups, or how to know when their baby should go to the doctor. 4. Create a healthy and positive attitude toward their baby
Turnaround Community Outreach provides hot meals to homeless and low income families and individuals once a week. In 2010 we served 2,978 hot meals during our regular lunch Program.

Turnaround Community Outreach provides free groceries and free clothing to homeless and low income families twice a month. In 2010, we served 1,594 individuals during our regular grocery and clothing giveaways. We served an additional 441 people with free clothing at Christmas time.

IRS990EZ.PrimaryExemptPurpose: "We desire to teach people how to rise above their current spiritual, physical, financial, and psychological condition. Through programs that teach people how to apply the Scriptures to their lives and equip them with the tools to succeed, we endeavor to give the poor and underserved the vision, hope, and confidence they need to transform their circumstances."
